com.amazon.ags.api.whispersync.migration
Interface MigrationCallback

public interface MigrationCallback

Callback used for one-time migration of V1 game data to the V2 game data format.

Method Summary
 void onComplete(MigrationResultCode result, byte[] data)
           
 

Method Detail

onComplete

void onComplete(MigrationResultCode result,
                byte[] data)
Parameters:
result - The result code from calling WhispersyncClient.migrateVersion1GameData().
data - The player's version 1.x game data in raw form. This value will only be non-null when the result code is is SUCCESS. If your game had previously used SynchronizeBlobCallback from version 1.x API, data is identical to what was received by onNewGameData(). If your game had previously used SynchronizeMultiFileCallback, you can unpack the game data using WhispersyncClient.unpackVersion1MultiFileGameData().
